    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
            <title>HOOD ADJUSTMENT AND ALIGNMENT</title>
            <para>The 8600 series front hood adjustment is done by moving the hinge plate attachment located at the
                front crossmember.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust the hood left to right</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the hinge attachment bolts and slide the hinge plate assemble left or
                        right.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the alignment with the hood contour lines. If the hood alignment is proper,
                        tighten the hinge plate bolts. Torque to required value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust hood forward and back (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900849">reference Figure 49</hotlnk>), loosen the hinge mounting bolts at the
                    mounting plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900849">Figure 49, Item 2</hotlnk>) on the front cross member.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Slide the hood forward or aft as required.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the distance between the rear edge of hood and clearance to windshield.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the hinge plate mounting bolts and torque to 50 to 55 lbf-ft (68 to 75
                        Nm).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900849" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900849.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Hood Hinge Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HINGE MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HINGE PLATE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
